When clicking on an opening bracket "{" in the code, atom highlights where the section starts and ends, like underlining the opening bracket { and the closing bracket }.

The problem is with comments. When writing a comment that contains brackets after an opening bracket, the highlighting is wrong, because Atom takes the comment into account. 
Example to try it out yourself:

```
    def classABC() {   // click on the bracket
      if () {

      }
      // }  Atom highlights this bracket, which is wrong
    }
```
